  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The pump operates continuously in vivo during extended cardiopulmonary bypass procedures lasting up to 6 hours, with the impeller subject to sustained rotational loads and the blood-contacting surfaces exposed to thrombogenic and protein-fouling conditions throughout the duty cycle.",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/cpb-hemolysis-worst-case",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cpb-hemolysis-rh-below-1",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/cfd-centrifugal-pump-hemolysis",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-generic-pump-experimental",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/cpb-flow-speed-matrix"
  ],
  "hasContextOfUse": {
    "decisionConsequence": "High",
    "description": "A CFD model is used to evaluate the sensitivity of pump-induced hemolysis to variations in component dimensions for a centrifugal blood pump used during cardiopulmonary bypass surgery. The device operates in vivo under continuous duty for procedures lasting up to 6 hours, with the pump running uninterrupted at rotational speeds between 2000 and 3500 RPM throughout. Blood temperature, viscosity, and protein composition vary over the extended in vivo duty cycle, and the pump bearings and seals are subject to sustained mechanical loading. Model influence is MEDIUM (testing confirms results); decision consequence is HIGH (incorrect tolerance decision could impact clinical hemolysis levels). Model Risk Level 2.",
    "deviceClass": "Class II",
    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cou/cou1-cpb",
    "intendedUse": "Use CFD to identify worst-case operating conditions for hemolysis across 5 flow-speed combinations for a Class II CPB device. Results compared against predicate device hemolysis using relative hemolysis index (RH < 1 acceptance criterion).",
    "modelInfluence": "Medium",
    "name": "COU1: Cardiopulmonary bypass use (Class II)",
    "type": "ContextOfUse"
  },
  "hasValidationResult": [
